  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/5078",
  "title": "feat: introduce `html` templating",
  "body": "⚠️ **DO NOT MERGE YET**\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR introduces `html` templating in InstantSearch.js.\r\n\r\nThis allows InstantSearch.js users to pass templates as HTML strings safely, with easier access to exposed data, and with an easier API to set up events.\r\n\r\n[**Read RFC →**](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch-rfcs/blob/master/accepted/html-templating-instantsearch.md)\r\n\r\n```js\r\ninstantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n  // ...\r\n  templates: {\r\n    item(hit, { html, components, sendEvent }) {\r\n      return html`<article>\r\n        <h2>${components.Highlight({ hit, attribute: 'name' })}</h2>\r\n        <p>${components.Snippet({ hit, attribute: 'description' })}</p>\r\n        <button\r\n          onClick=\"${() => sendEvent('conversion', hit, 'Product Added')}\"\r\n        >\r\n          Add to cart\r\n        </button>\r\n      </article>`;\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Review\r\n\r\n### Tests\r\n\r\n**This feature involves many tests in a lot of widgets, along with fixes in a buncg of existing types. To keep the changes digestible, I've added widget-level tests in a separate PR.**\r\n\r\n### New components\r\n\r\nThe PR introduces new VDOM components: `Highlight`, `Snippet`, `ReverseHighlight`, and `ReverseSnippet` which are exposed in the templates of the `hits` and `infiniteHits` widgets.\r\n\r\nThey depend on a common implementation from [`ui-components/highlight-vdom`](https://github.com/algolia/ui-components/tree/master/packages/highlight-vdom) and are wrapped  internally to add the InstantSearch-specific class names. This wrapping will have to be done in every VDOM-based flavor. In the future, we may want to move those in a separate `instantsearch-vdom` package.\r\n\r\nThe final components exposed in templates live in `src/helpers/components/` (with the logic to parse hits and pass parts to the UI component), near their existing string-based counterparts.\r\n\r\n### CI failures\r\n\r\nSome checks don't pass, notably the type checks for `geoSearch` because the `HTMLMarker` is currently designed to work with plain HTML. I'll fix this in a dedicated PR.",
